        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks for "rich and valuable" letter [missing].</p> 
<p>Has read TR’s paper in <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi> ["Seedling fruits – plums", (1863): 27] – "a treasure to me".</p> 
            <p>Questions about seedling peaches that approach almonds.</p>
            <p>Asks whether TR has ever observed varieties of plants growing close to other varieties for several generations without being affected by crossing.</p>
        </abstract>
